The paper deals with zero-shot learning for image recognition, which is a problem in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper proposes a novel algorithm for multi-label zero-shot learning, which involves learning intermediate semantic representations and exploiting correlations between labels. This suggests that the paper could also be classified under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of semantic word vectors, which are commonly used in natural language processing (cs.CL). Finally, the experiments involve standard multi-label datasets, which are often used in multimedia analysis (cs.MM).
